   "id": "22d41dfa-c12b-4725-a4d0-e412f58b8c53",

   "source": [
    "# Introduction to `ospgrid`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0e448ab2-3d3b-42aa-9fce-ab4c6742b403",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "`ospgrid` provides a user-friendly interface to OpenSeesPy for the analysis of elastic plane grids.\n",
    "This tutorial shows its basic use."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "96593ef5-cc0a-40db-9921-8a9249b4c4ac",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# This cell not necessary once ospgrid is installed\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append(\"../../..\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "22f803ab-23c7-4872-ba27-12b4faf641c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Basic imports\n",
    "import ospgrid as ospg  # The main package\n",
    "from IPython import display  # For images in this notebook"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3a8e7a81-189b-42e5-a0f4-96122b8f5bbf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Example 1\n",
    "This example is based on the Semester 1 2021 Exam question for the class *CIV4280 Bridge Design & Assessment* at Monash University, Melbourne.\n",
    "\n",
    "We consider the following grid, taking the following for all members:\n",
    "\n",
    "- $EI = 10\\times10^3$ kNm2\n",
    "- $GJ = 5\\times 10^3$ kNm2\n",
    "\n",
    "To keep units consistent, we will maintain forces in kN and distances in m.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "b76e2fb0-12a1-43ec-a6f8-0c038bb89c73",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid = ospg.Grid()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "a4fae2f8-e743-45d8-bff2-aae4d403c03d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "width": 800
      }
     },
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "display.Image(\"./images/intro_ex_1.png\",width=800)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "426dbd9c-a9b8-4d25-b82a-8c4160f9c04c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Taking node $E$ as the origin of the coordinate system, using user-friendly labels, we define the nodes then as:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "caf52191-852e-4bf7-8e5c-3a746f003fe1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid.add_node(\"A\", -2.0, 0.0)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"B\", 0.0, 4.75)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"C\", 4.0, 0.0)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"D\", 0.0, -4.0)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"E\", 0.0, 0.0);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "368f242e-e884-4b89-bc19-ea604ed3e363",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And similarly, for the members, we set the flexural and torsional rigidities and add members connecting the relevant nodes, using the nice labelling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "c1828630-07d3-41f5-b8fd-cd2e266f926e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "EI = 10e3 # kNm2\n",
    "GJ = 5e3\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"A\", \"E\", EI, GJ)\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"B\", \"E\", EI, GJ)\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"C\", \"E\", EI, GJ)\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"D\", \"E\", EI, GJ);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "907037a1-5ef7-4874-9bc3-6a137833b614",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The loads are added similarly, using intuitive arguments:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "c3d1cdce-dd2d-44ef-85c0-391ec996ff92",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid.add_load(\"E\", Fz=-90, Mx=30, My=60)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8280e715-58bb-4109-a4c9-a2e77c15ada3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And supports are defined by adding a pre-defined support type to a node."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "7d937834-8ae8-4d44-a17f-366ce165653f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid.add_support(\"B\", ospg.Support.FIXED)\n",
    "grid.add_support(\"C\", ospg.Support.FIXED)\n",
    "grid.add_support(\"D\", ospg.Support.FIXED)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b1e27e1f-ef9e-4603-a6c3-0bc9401db0a8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And now we can run the analysis:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "c8d906e8-6809-4e63-b77f-1a93f728daae",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops = grid.analyze()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ad20876-605a-4bed-b09e-1db2119527bf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And extract all of the displacements for a node:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "c082586b-9afa-4546-bffd-ecb4ac3ef149",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[0.0, 0.0, -0.019106528912442664, 0.0004656650928675513, -0.0009469098824023142, 0.0]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dE = grid.get_displacement(\"E\")\n",
    "print(dE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "094a28a4-b318-4612-82f9-77c7f856a166",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also get the reactions at a node, and here we get just one we are interested in (vertical force reaction):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "2628658e-b7d1-413e-872d-57f0bb8e6c8c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "20.155184539095423\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rB = grid.get_reactions(\"B\", dof=3)\n",
    "print(rB)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "68130ad1-58f0-40db-9250-b1e7e9dc85cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we can plot the results:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "43dad504-b855-41d8-8068-2f494e489065",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     },

    },

     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "grid.plot_results();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2351baf3-4c31-40bb-8cb8-8771768b0bd8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Example 2\n",
    "\n",
    "This example is based on the Semester 1 2020 Exam question for the same class as *Example 1*.\n",
    "\n",
    "We consider the following grid, taking the following for all members:\n",
    "\n",
    "- $EI = 30\\times10^3$ kNm2\n",
    "- $GJ = 5\\times 10^3$ kNm2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "43f55c90-0a32-4940-94fd-5684e64414fa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "width": 800
      }
     },
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "display.Image(\"./images/intro_ex_2.png\",width=800)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "344ff4e9-3702-4855-a67d-7827185df4b9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Make a new grid object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "02e4f40c-38ea-46c2-aef6-6d18a8be57e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid = ospg.Grid()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f1d4bb16-c243-4b1b-bdcb-8f23db7b07fa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As before, taking node $E$ as the origin of the coordinate system, the nodes are defined as:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "9478e7ea-a4b8-4018-a1b8-7a6db3806e40",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid.add_node(\"A\", -2.5, 0.0)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"B\", 0.0, 3.5)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"C\", 5.0, 0.0)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"D\", 0.0, -5.0)\n",
    "grid.add_node(\"E\", 0.0, 0.0);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0bb3a7ba-4b2f-458e-9e00-cca3894ab0cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And similarly, for the members, we set the flexural and torsional rigidities and add members connecting the relevant nodes, using the nice labelling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "18cb6a73-fe07-4fc6-ba2c-0be014f44a0a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "EI = 30e3 # kNm2\n",
    "GJ = 5e3\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"A\", \"E\", EI, GJ)\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"B\", \"E\", EI, GJ)\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"C\", \"E\", EI, GJ)\n",
    "grid.add_member(\"D\", \"E\", EI, GJ);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0cb53771-a64f-4e5c-9753-f69a547f30f3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The loads are added similarly, using intuitive arguments in consistent units (kN and kNm):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "4c2c5b2a-0282-4046-810d-8d7f8bab7ff2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid.add_load(\"A\", Fz=-130)\n",
    "grid.add_load(\"E\", Mx=10, My=20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d2c93178-b2d6-4894-b213-f8e4fa972559",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And supports are defined by adding a pre-defined support type to a node.\n",
    "Note that a `PROP` is different to a `PINNED` support as it only restrains translation in the $z$-axis. In contrast, a `PINNED` support also restrains the twist of the connecting member (hence `PINNED_X` and `PINNED_Y`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "d856299e-6819-4d15-9900-5c4993b2ea7a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid.add_support(\"A\", ospg.Support.FIXED_V_ROLLER)\n",
    "grid.add_support(\"B\", ospg.Support.FIXED)\n",
    "grid.add_support(\"C\", ospg.Support.FIXED)\n",
    "grid.add_support(\"D\", ospg.Support.FIXED)\n",
    "grid.add_support(\"E\", ospg.Support.PROP)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "21942420-de3f-488e-90bf-b07f3f9fd3bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And now we can run the analysis:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "645ec8f9-76ab-41d2-8aa6-12e0b6a63673",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops = grid.analyze()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "470b463c-04ba-4f1f-92dc-e7b03b6886b4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we can selectively plot the grid and bending moment diagram, changing some plotting parameters too, for example:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "24668763-6143-4b49-93f4-a3d23d379066",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "grid.plot_grid(figsize=(6,6),axes_on=True);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "id": "5f2dc1eb-f61b-4c7c-90c0-5c55cae7bfb6",
   "metadata": {},

     },

      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "grid.plot_bmd(figsize=(8,8),axes_on=False);"
   ]
  },
